            <p>STATE OF NEW YORK&#44;<lb/>
                Assembly Chamber<lb/>
                N. Y <del>Albany</del> May 5 1889<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Dr<lb/></p>
            <p>I learn from Dr H P Mendes that the<lb/> Advisory Board&#44; at their meeting attended by you<lb/> have agreed to have a public examination of<lb/> seminary students on Sunday May 26th&#45;&#45;<lb/> such action is approved by the Trustees&#44; &#38;<lb/> although I believe Dr Cohen does not agree<lb/> with the advisability of same&#44; the general<lb/> sentiment is&#44; that it is time to show we<lb/> are still alive&#44; and to have the community<lb/> know it&#45;&#45;I hope therefore&#44; that you will<lb/> in connection with Dr Mendes&#44; and Dr<lb/> Drachman arrange the programme of<lb/> exercises&#44; not for any particular show or<lb/> display&#44; but simply for a public examination<lb/> to evidence the progress our students have<lb/> made &#38;c&#44; and whatever else your good<lb/> judgment may determine&#45;&#45;please also<lb/> consult Dr Cohen as to same&#45;&#45;I shall<lb/> write to him also to&#45;day&#44; and sincerely<lb/> trust that all may be well&#44; and redound<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to the benefit of our Seminary &#38;c&#45;&#45;<lb/> Please see to it&#44; that nothing shall<lb/> interfere with your certain presence<lb/> here on that day&#44; and that Dr Jastrow<lb/> will also be here&#45;&#45;the hour is set for<lb/> 2<hi rend="sup">30</hi> P. M&#45;&#45;Excuse me for having over&#45;<lb/>looked the mention you made of the kind<lb/> intention of Mr Sulzberger to send those<lb/> Books&#45;&#45;certainly the freight and binding<lb/> of Books&#44; will gladly be paid by us&#44; with<lb/> many thanks to Mr S&#45;&#45;If you have<lb/> any suggestions to offer&#44; please do so&#44; as<lb/> soon as possible&#44; and with perfect<lb/> freedom&#45;&#45;I wish you can arrange<lb/> to stay until a later train on eveng of<lb/> the 26th&#44; so that we can talk over<lb/> some matters&#45;&#45;<lb/>  In haste<lb/> Yours very truly<lb/> Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            <p>I have asked Dr Cohen&#44; whether it would be<lb/> well to have an examining <sic>committe</sic> of<lb/> say yourself&#44; Kohut &#38; Jastrow&#44; or is it<lb/> better that yourself&#44; Drachman &#38; Lieberman<lb/> shall examine the students<lb/></p>
            </body>
